As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 134 people, 98 households, and 64 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2020: Cloud Lake town, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Cloud+Lake+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1101|access-date=June 22, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 135 people, 77 households, and 46 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2010: Cloud Lake town, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Cloud+Lake+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101|access-date=September 26, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 167 people, 62 households, and 43 families residing in the town. The [[population density]] was 1,074.7/km{{sup|2}} (2,651.8/mi<sup>2</sup>). There were 68 housing units at an average density of 437.6/km{{sup|2}} (1,079.8/mi<sup>2</sup>). The racial makeup of the town was 87.43% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] (68.9% [[Non-Hispanic White]]),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.muninetguide.com/states/florida/municipality/Cloud_Lake.php |title=Demographics of Cloud Lake, FL |publisher=MuniNetGuide.com |accessdate=November 14, 2007}}</ref> 2.99% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 7.78% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 1.80% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 30.54% of the population.

In 2000, there were 62 households out of which 30.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 56.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.7% had a female householder with no husband present, and 30.6% were non-families. 25.8% of all households were made up of individuals and 9.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.69 and the average family size was 3.33. The median income for a household in the town was $55,625, and the median income for a family was $57,292. Males had a median income of $31,250 versus $30,833 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $24,311. None of the population or families were below the [[poverty line]].

As of 2000, [[English language|English]] was the [[first language]] of 100% of its residents. It, along with [[Briny Breezes, Florida|Briny Breezes]], [[Golf, Florida|Golf]], and [[Jupiter Inlet Colony, Florida|Jupiter Inlet Colony]]  were the only [[municipality|municipalities]] in Palm Beach county with all residents having the [[mother tongue]] of English.<ref>{{cite web |url=
http://www.mla.org/map_data_results&state_id=12&county_id=&mode=place&zip=&place_id=13050&cty_id=&ll=&a=&ea=&order=r |title=MLA Data Center Results of Cloud Lake, FL |publisher=[[Modern Language Association]] |accessdate=November 14, 2007}}</ref>

